</p></div><FILENAME filename="requirements.html"><html><head><title>Requirements</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="help:/common/kde-default.css" type="text/css"><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.48"><meta name="keywords" content="KDE, yammi, mp3, ogg, wav, tag, fuzzy search, digital music, collection, organization"><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><meta name="GENERATOR" content="KDE XSL Stylesheet V1.13 using libxslt"><link rel="home" href="index.html" title="The yammi 1.2-beta Handbook"><link rel="up" href="install.html" title="Chapter 2. Installation"><link rel="previous" href="install.html" title="Chapter 2. Installation"><link rel="next" href="compileAndInstall.html" title="Compilation and installation"></head><body bgcolor="white" text="black" link="#0000FF" vlink="#840084" alink="#0000FF"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr class="header"><td colspan="2"> </td></tr><tr id="logo"><td valign="top"><img src="help:/common/kde_logo.png" alt="KDE -         The K Desktop Environment" width="296" height="79" border="0"></td><td valign="middle" align="center" id="location"><h1>Requirements</h1></td></tr></table><table width="100%" class="header"><tbody><tr><td align="left" class="navLeft" width="33%"><a accesskey="p" href="install.html">Prev</a></td><td align="center" class="navCenter" width="34%">Installation</td><td align="right" class="navRight" width="33%"> 
		      <a accesskey="n" href="compileAndInstall.html">Next</a></td></tr></tbody></table><div class="sect1"><div class="titlepage"><div><h2 class="title" style="clear: both"><a name="requirements"></a>Requirements</h2></div></div><div class="sect2"><div class="titlepage"><div><h3 class="title"><a name="id2837457"></a>Mandatory</h3></div></div><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>
<a href="http://www.trolltech.com/products/qt/" target="_top">Trolltech's QT</a>, version 3.x
</p></li><li><p>
libstdc++
</p></li></ul></div></div><div class="sect2"><div class="titlepage"><div><h3 class="title"><a name="id2837495"></a>Optional (but recommended)</h3></div></div><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>
For reading id3 tags: <a href="http://www.id3lib.org" target="_top">id3lib</a>, version 3.8.2 or higher
(recommended: newest version) (-lid3 -lz)
</p></li><li><p>
For reading ogg tags and layer information: 
<a href="http://www.vorbis.com/download_unix.psp" target="_top">libvorbis, libvorbisfile and libogg</a>
(-lvorbisfile -lvorbis -logg)
</p></li><li><p>
For XMMS support:
<a href="http://www.xmms.org" target="_top">XMMS</a>, version 1.2.6 or later
and glib (-lgtk -lgdk -lgmodule -lglib -ldl -lXi -lXext -lX11 -lm -lxmms)
</p></li><li><p>
For listening to songs on a second soundcard during playback on your primary soundcard
you need the command line tools mpg123 (for mp3 files), ogg123 (for ogg files) or play (for wav files).
</p></li><li><p>
If you want to use the ripping and encoding function offered from within yammi,
you need cdparanoia and (not)lame or other ripping/encoding tools, for details have a look
at the script "yammiGrabAndEncode" included in the distribution.
</p></li><li><p>
If you want to use certain plugins you might need other programs
(such as k3b for the "Burn with K3b" plugins or cdlabelgen for the "Create CD Label" plugin).
</p></li></ul></div></div><div class="sect2"><div class="titlepage"><div><h3 class="title"><a name="id2792436"></a>...for compiling from source</h3></div></div><p>
If you want to compile Yammi from source, you need additionally to the above
mentioned requirements the following packages installed:
</p><div class="sect3"><div class="titlepage"><div><h4 class="title"><a name="id2792450"></a>Mandatory</h4></div></div><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>
Xfree86-devel
</p></li><li><p>
qt3-devel
</p></li></ul></div></div><div class="sect3"><div class="titlepage"><div><h4 class="title"><a name="id2792479"></a>Optional</h4></div></div><div class="itemizedlist"><ul type="disc"><li><p>
For reading id3 tags: libz
</p></li><li><p>
For reading ogg tags and layer information: libvorbis-dev
</p></li><li><p>
For XMMS support: xmms-devel
</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><table width="100%" class="bottom-nav"><tr><td width="33%" align="left" valign="top" class="navLeft"><a href="install.html">Prev</a></td><td width="34%" align="center" valign="top" class="navCenter"><a href="index.html">Home</a></td><td width="33%" align="right" valign="top" class="navRight"><a href="compileAndInstall.html">Next</a></td></tr><tr><td width="33%" align="left" class="navLeft">Installation </td><td width="34%" align="center" class="navCenter"><a href="install.html">Up</a></td><td width="33%" align="right" class="navRight"> Compilation and installation</td></tr></table></body></html></FILENAME><FILENAME filename="compileAndInstall.html"><html><head><title>Compilation and installation</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="help:/common/kde-default.css" type="text/css"><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.48"><meta name="keywords" content="KDE, yammi, mp3, ogg, wav, tag, fuzzy search, digital music, collection, organization"><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><meta name="GENERATOR" content="KDE XSL Stylesheet V1.13 using libxslt"><link rel="home" href="index.html" title="The yammi 1.2-beta Handbook"><link rel="up" href="install.html" title="Chapter 2. Installation"><link rel="previous" href="requirements.html" title="Requirements"><link rel="next" href="problems.html" title="Problems"></head><body bgcolor="white" text="black" link="#0000FF" vlink="#840084" alink="#0000FF"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr class="header"><td colspan="2"> </td></tr><tr id="logo"><td valign="top"><img src="help:/common/kde_logo.png" alt="KDE -         The K Desktop Environment" width="296" height="79" border="0"></td><td valign="middle" align="center" id="location"><h1>Compilation and installation</h1></td></tr></table><table width="100%" class="header"><tbody><tr><td align="left" class="navLeft" width="33%"><a accesskey="p" href="requirements.html">Prev</a></td><td align="center" class="navCenter" width="34%">Installation</td><td align="right" class="navRight" width="33%"> 
		      <a accesskey="n" href="problems.html">Next</a></td></tr></tbody></table><div class="sect1"><div class="titlepage"><div><h2 class="title" style="clear: both"><a name="compileAndInstall"></a>Compilation and installation</h2></div></div><p>
Before compilation, verify that an environment variable named "KDEDIR" points to your KDE installation
(to check, type "export" in a shell and verify that KDEDIR is set to the proper directory).
If this variable is not set, proper installation into the correct directories cannot be guaranteed,
and your most likely better off to type "export KDEDIR=/opt/kde3" to set this variable (using a bash and assuming that KDE was installed to /opt/kde3).

In order to compile and install Yammi on your system, type the following in
the base directory of the Yammi distribution:
</p><p>&gt; ./configure</p><p>&gt; make</p><p>&gt; make install</p><p>
If compilation is successful, the executable "yammi" and some other files will be installed to your KDE directories.
